<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1864-05-11T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1864-05-11T00:00:00-05:00" n="361" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d361">
                        <head><persName type="from">Mr. Pike</persName> to <persName type="to">Mr.
                                Seward</persName></head>
                        <opener>
                            <seg rendition="#left">No. 132.]</seg>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">United States Legation,</hi>
                                    <hi rend="italic">The Hague,</hi></placeName>
                                <date calendar="gregorian" when="1864-05-11"><hi rend="italic">May</hi> 11, 1864.</date></dateline></opener>
                        <p><hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: The United States government steamer
                            Kearsarge has made her appearance at Flushing, in the island of
                            Walcheren, with the object of making some repairs.</p>
                        <p>At the instance of the commander, Captain Winslow, I have procured
                            liberty from the minister of marine for the ship to enter the government
                            dock at that port for this purpose.</p>
                        <p>I have the honor to be, with great respect, your most obedient
                            servant,</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>JAMES S. PIKE,</signed></closer>
                        <postscript>
                            <p>Hon. <hi rend="smallcaps">William H. Seward,</hi>
                                <hi rend="italic">Secretary of State, Washington.</hi></p>
                        </postscript>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>